			<div class="content" id="post-content-572066">
									

<p>Seconding the Experiment Log. Potential test materials: a book with no setting, like a corporate annual report; a book with no apparent library, study, or such location; a poetry collection; a coloring book; a reference book, like a dictionary, phone book, or technical manual; the script from a play; an orchestral score; and (oh gods I'm gonna get crucified for suggesting this) Cassie.</p>
<p>Other questions:<br />
If 826 doesn't kick in till the subject leaves the room, does it only transform empty rooms?<br />
As the subject leaves the room, can he tell what the containment room transforms into?<br />
Can subjects communicate with the outside world via radio or satellite?<br />
How do we know what happens to subjects stuck in the book when 826 resets?<br />
Does time within 826 flow at the same speed as the outside world?</p>

